# Project Guide

Before working on any task, read `AGENTS.md` at the project root for:
- Project architecture and directory structure
- Code conventions (naming, format, style)
- Important rules (protected files, required checks)
- How to add routes, pages, dependencies
- How to run the project

Key rules:
- Do NOT modify `.env`, `uploads/*`, `dist/*`, or `package-lock.json` directly
- Read related files before editing
- Check linter after edits
- Follow existing patterns: camelCase JS, PascalCase components, snake_case Python
- New API routes must be mounted in server.js and added to frontend api.js
